sentences: Ingrid Jensen (born January 12, 1966) is a Canadian jazz trumpeter.
Jensen was born in North Vancouver and grew up in Nanaimo.
She received a scholarship to the Berklee College of Music in Boston.
After graduating from Berklee, she toured with the Vienna Art Orchestra and taught at the Bruckner Conservatory in Austria when she was 25.
She went back to the U.S. in 1994 and became a member of the DIVA Big Band.
She went back to the U.S. in 1994 and became a member of the DIVA Big Band. During the same year, her debut album Vernal Fields (Enja, 1994) appeared and won a Juno Award.
She has performed on Saturday Night Live with the British soul singer Corrine Bailey Rae and in the horn section backing actor Denis Leary.
